Title: Page 1
Description.note: The first document, dated 1766, deals with a piece of land owned by Pascuala Maria, the widow of Diego Martin, and her son, Juan Partino, from San Lorenzo.

Title: Page 4
Description.note: The second document (bound to the first), dated 1804, is written in Spanish. In it, Doña Maria de la Merced, widow of Don Luis Bartolome Fernandez, from the barrio of Espiritu Santo, demonstrates that she purchased the land in the previous document in 1766, and now wishes to sell it to Don Juan Jose Rosano. Both documents bear the stamp of King Carolus IV.
